.........................................20.20-Day-10_Persistant_Mounting_Using_FSTAB..............................................................

to make system automaticaly mount partitions whene rebooting

we must save some configrations in some configration file

the configration file will be :

/etc/fstab :this file contain configration to file system tables 

-so it have table of file system that we want to mount in the system 

file system table would be like :

 <file system>     <mount point>    <type>    <options>                      <dump>                 <pass>
                                                               
   file system        /media/         type      read/write execute            backup from zero to 9 for the order of dumpe file                    to check file system        the order of checking partitions
                                       of 
                                      file 
                                      system
        path
    /dev/nvme0n2p1



NOTE: be cearfule in editing that file (/etc/fstab)


NOTE: we can use command to have no broplem with booting the machine


command: mount -a

                                                                                
┌──(root㉿kali)-[/dev]
└─# mount -a                    
mount: /etc/fstab: parse error at line 17 -- ignored
                            
this command tell us that we have error at line and ignored it 


and tell kernl to mount the device i write in


...................
NOTE : if we reboot the system and have some sentax error in the fstab file the system can be ignore that error and enter you in mentainans moode to solve tha problme


..........................................................................................................

NOTE:

NOTE:

NOTE;


each partition you mount will copied info about it in file :/etc/mtab (mounted filesystemtable)

we can viwe that file and take the last line of it and place it into the file (/dev/fstab)

to hvae no problem in that file so 

1- creat partition
2- creat file system for it 
3-partprobe the partition
4-mount the partition 
5-cat /etc/mtab
6-copy the line of the partition you mounted 
7- place it into /etc/fstab
........

NOTE: to delet partition be sure that partition isnot in file (/etc/fstab)

delet it from fstab too.


